{"key":"post-9781984","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9781984</id>\n<content>You really want to fruit at normal room temperature of +/- 25C.&amp;nbsp; You have to remember that fresh air is the number 1 pinning trigger, once you have your substrate fully colonized.&amp;nbsp; If you want to heat an old refrigerator to that temperature, it will be fine for colonizing your jars, but it's not the best for fruiting.&amp;nbsp; If you 'have' to use that attic, I'd wait and start your jars about three weeks before your temperature in that area averages around 23C to 27C.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Best is to put your fruiting chamber in the house in your bedroom, where it will be at normal room temp.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9782029</next>\n<prev>9781028</prev>\n<first>9780473</first>\n<last>9784282</last>\n<when>1234419928</when>\n<utime>02/12/09 08:25 AM</utime>\n</post>"}